ZH: 我的腿突然僵住了，走不动了。
EN: My leg suddenly stiffened and I couldn't walk anymore.

ZH: 看到蛇，他吓得整个人都僵住了。
EN: He was so scared when he saw the snake that he froze completely.

ZH: 那只狐狸发现我正在观察它，它僵住了，然后悄悄离开了。
EN: The fox noticed that I was observing it, it froze, and then quietly left.

ZH: 当我听到她的名字时，我的心仿佛僵住了一样。
EN: When I heard her name, it felt like my heart froze.

ZH: 孩子们画图时，我建议他们养成不要僵住的好习惯。
EN: When the children are drawing, I suggest they develop the habit of not freezing up.

ZH: 紧张的情绪使得演讲者僵住了。
EN: The nervousness caused the speaker to freeze up.

ZH: 在漫长的比赛中，他们的注意力逐渐僵住了。
EN: During the long competition, their attention gradually froze.

ZH: 她尴尬地僵住了，不知道该怎么开口。
EN: She froze awkwardly, unsure of how to speak.

ZH: 僵住的场面使整个房间变得死一般的安静。
EN: The frozen scene made the whole room deadly quiet.

ZH: 他的表情僵住了，无法掩饰内心的失望。
EN: His expression froze, unable to hide his disappointment.

ZH: 突如其来的恶劣天气令人僵住。
EN: The sudden bad weather caused people to freeze in their tracks.

ZH: 那个惊人的发现使得他整个人都僵住了。
EN: The astonishing discovery froze him completely.

ZH: 孩子吓得僵住了，不敢再往前走了。
EN: The child froze in fear and didn't dare to go any further.

ZH: 当我听到那个消息时，我整个人都僵住了。
EN: When I heard that news, I froze completely.

ZH: 在紧急情况下，很多人会僵住，不知道该怎么办。
EN: In emergency situations, many people freeze and don't know what to do.

ZH: 这个笑话太搞笑了，让我笑得僵住了。
EN: This joke is so funny that it made me freeze up with laughter.

ZH: 当她听到音乐时，她的身体情不自禁地僵住了一下。
EN: When she heard the music, her body involuntarily stiffened for a moment.

ZH: 当警报响起时，人们都僵住了，等待着进一步的指示。
EN: When the alarm went off, everyone froze in anticipation of further instructions.

ZH: 这个问题使我完全僵住了，不知道该怎么回答。
EN: This question completely froze me, and I didn't know how to respond.

ZH: 在这寒冷的冬天，湖面僵住了。
EN: The lake froze over during this cold winter.
